fields.question: How often does a hen lay eggs?
fields.answer: It is a little bit different from different type of hens. For example Burma hen usually lays an egg a day.

fields.name: Bantam
fields.information:
Bantam is a dwarf chicken breed that came to Europe in the mid-19th century from Java in Indonesia. The breed is not very good as a laying hen, but is more of a hobby breed, among other things for show.
A hen weighs about 500 grams. The eggs are white and weigh about 25 grams.

In their own way, bantam are active hens that have good flying ability. If they are kept fenced outdoors, nets are often needed over the fence as well. They are easily tamed and the individuals are often sociable by themselves.

fields.name: Guinea fowl
fields.information: Guinea fowl are large birds that measure between 40 and 71 cm and weigh 700–1,600 grams. They feed on insects and seeds, and nest directly on the ground. They lack feathers on the head and the plumage is mainly gray-spotted.

fields.name: Brahma
fields.information:
The Brahman is a large breed, a hen weighs about 4 kilograms.
In the past, brahman was kept mainly as a breed of meat, but also for his eggs. Today, it no longer has any significance as a production breed for meat because it grows too slowly for meat production on a larger scale to be economical. Instead, it is now more of a chicken breed that is kept for fun and as an exhibition breed.

The eggs are comparatively small, an egg of a large hen weighs about 55 grams and has a yellow-brown shell color. 

In its own way, the Brahman is a calm race that is rarely aggressive.

fields.name: Lohman
fields.information:
The hen is considered the world's most effective laying hybrid. It lays about 340 eggs a year. The eggs are brown and weigh about 70 grams.

Unlike white Lohmann hens, the brown Lohmann is about 180-200 grams heavier and weighs 1.9-2.1 kg at 60 weeks of age. The hen Lohmann silver is reminiscent of the brown one but has white feathers and lays slightly smaller eggs.

Brown Lohmann is a relatively calm hybrid; the plumage is brown with hints of white.
